review.body: Thanks very much for this improvement. I can't claim to understand (hence, approve) everything, but I took the liberty to add our brand-new Apple M1 CI to check whether everything tests OK on that platform with gcc-11 -- and it seems it still doesn't: It's [picnic --not coming from PQClean failing](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/pull/1177/checks?check_run_id=4863789372), though. @christianpaquin : Do you know whether it should work on ARM64 compiled with gcc-11?

pull_request.title: Fixed build issue on arm based macs when using gcc11
pull_request.body:
This resolves #1164. This pr also updates the CMakeLists.txt template for copy_from_upstream so that all KEM implementations we pull from pqclean define `old_gas_syntax` when run on Darwin. This is so that in the future, as more aarch64 optimized implementations are added to pqclean and eventually liboqs, the assembly files will need to be updated such that all instances of `#ifndef __clang__` become `#if !defined(__clang__) && !defined(old_gas_syntax)`.

As a result, some non-saber/kyber CMakeLists.txt's are also updated in this PR to defined `old_gas_syntax` on darwin.
